Under general direction, provides support to a wide variety of Human Resources programs including staffing, human resources information systems (HRIS), classification/compensation, benefits, record maintenance, and compliance with state and federal regulations concerning Human Resources Administration.
 Examples of Duties:
Performs a variety of technical duties in support of the City's employment, recruitment, and selection process;
Maintains a variety of files and records related to employees and applicants;
Assists with the employee evaluation process, sends notifications to management, and tracks completion;
Reviews, verifies, and processes request for tuition reimbursement; tracks and maintains expenditure records;
Participates in the employee onboarding process including orientation, processing paperwork, and verifying work eligibility;
Processes personnel changes regarding employee status, salary, and personal information;
Participates in the administration of the employee benefit program;
Participates in special projects;
Answers questions and provides information to the general public and city or department staff;
Conducts studies, analysis and research on a broad range of personnel assignments;
Administers human resources information systems;
Writes queries and prepares reports;
Evaluates human resources information system needs and identifies appropriate applications to meet the needs of various departments;
Creates and determines best uses of databases for various research projects;
Provides general assistance to the overall administration of the human resources department;
Attends meetings as assigned and stays abreast of new trends and information in the field of human resources; and
Performs other related duties as assigned.
 Qualifications:
Education:
Equivalent to an associate's degree from an accredited college or university with major course work in business or public administration, human resources, or a related field.
Experience:
One year of increasingly responsible experience in a variety of areas related to human resources administration or personnel management.
Experience in a public agency is desirable.
Licenses and Certificates:
Possession of an appropriate, valid driver's license.
Special Requirements:
Essential functions and duties require the following physical abilities and work environment:
Ability to work in a standard office environment; ability to travel to different sites and locations; ability to sit, stand, walk, kneel, stoop, crawl, twist and climb; exposure to heat, noise, outdoors, chemicals, confining work space, mechanical hazards, and electrical hazards; lift, drag and push files, reports, or other materials weighing up to 25 pounds is also required.

The Director of Government Relations will be the primary liaison for and ensure positive organizational relationships with the key state-level stakeholders/policy actors (governmental and non-governmental) with direct authority and/or indirect influence over education policy functions/programs and resource allocations. This role will be responsible for the design and execution of strategic plans intended to raise the visibility of Edmentum within target states. Anticipation and identification of legislative challenges and opportunities is critical. We are looking for someone who has a positive can do attitude highly motivated to learn and a creative thinker that can provide practical approaches to support a quickly changing organization.

Edmentum is committed to making it easier for educators to individualize learning for every student through simple technology high-quality content actionable data and customer success. Founded in innovation Edmentums powerful learning solutions blend technology with individual teaching approaches. We are dedicated to being educators' most trusted partner in creating successful student outcomes everywhere learning occurs. Our commitment is built off the emphasis we place on our core values: passion people respect collaboration and performance.
The Director of Government Relations will be the primary liaison for and ensure positive organizational relationships with the key state-level stakeholders/policy actors (governmental and non-governmental) with direct authority and/or indirect influence over education policy functions/programs and resource allocations. This role will be responsible for the design and execution of strategic plans intended to raise the visibility of Edmentum within target states. Anticipation and identification of legislative challenges and opportunities is critical. We are looking for someone who has a positive can do attitude highly motivated to learn and a creative thinker that can provide practical approaches to support a quickly changing organization. This is a home office position that can be located anywhere in the US.

Here's what you'll do:
Cultivate relationships with policy makers
Act as the key interface between external consultants public relations firms and government relations firms;
Support and act as primary conduit between Sales and external constituents;
Play an integral role in conference strategy;
Gather information on relevant policy thinking and report to Executive Leadership team;
Identify strategic alliances within target states;
Manage government relations agreements and assess performance;
Represent Edmentum at conference and partner events;
Assist in development of messaging and positioning;
Management of partner contracts and budget;
Collaborate with Sales Services and Marketing to develop strategic plan and State Solutions approach;
Monthly briefs with Field Sales and Sales Operations teams.

Here's what you'll need:
Bachelors Degree required
Knowledge and expertise in Education policy and legislative affairs
Minimum 10+ years experience in government relations/public affairs multi state representation is preferred
Experience and proven ability to work and thrive in a cross-functional role with success in aligning goals and objectives and balancing competing interests and priorities
Proven track record of interpreting relevant insights from various resources to spot trends
Strong organization presentation negotiation and interpersonal skills
Confidence and ability to thrive in a fast-paced and dynamic team environment
Good customer focus attitude and excellent interpersonal verbal and written communication skills
Edmentum is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race color religion sex gender identity sexual orientation national origin disability status protected veteran status or any other characteristic protected by law.

$39,437 - $54,309 a yearPerforms a variety of general office clerical and administrative support duties for the Public Works Department programs and activities; performs related work as required.

Considerable leeway is granted for the exercise of independent judgment and initiative.

Position Schedule: Monday-Friday, 7:30a.m.-4:30p.m.

(Promotion opportunity to Administrative Assistant II ($19.95-$27.41/hr) possible based on time in the position and performance.)
Examples of Duties / Knowledge & Skills

Prepares and composes correspondences, reports, lists and other documents for Public Works programs and staff;
Interprets and applies departmental or office rules, policies and regulations in accordance with prescribed procedures and guidelines;
Copies, packages and distributes a variety of written materials to meet program requirements;
Organizes and prioritizes work assignments and provides work direction to other support staff;
Gathers, assembles, updates, distributes and/or files a variety of information, forms, records and data as requested;
Responds to and directs complaints from the public relating to department operations taking appropriate action to resolve and refer such complaints;
Supports customer service operations and answers department telephone calls, receives and greets visitors to the department and provides information or refers callers and visitors to other appropriate departments;
Requisitions supplies and materials for the department as requested in accordance with Purchasing Services regulations;
Takes verbatim dictation and transcribes or prepares letters, minutes, reports and other related materials;
Performs all work duties and activities in accordance with City policies, procedures and safety practices;
Attends work regularly at the designated place and time;
Supports continuous process improvement initiatives;
Performs related work as required.
Minimum qualifications & Requirements
Required Knowledge and Abilities:
Thorough knowledge of modern office procedures, practices and equipment;
Thorough knowledge of modern office filing systems and procedures;
Good knowledge of departmental programs, policies and operations as applied to the work performed;
Ability to operate a personal computer using program applications appropriate to assigned duties and responsibilities;
Ability to maintain complex clerical records and prepare reports;
Ability to organize and prioritize work assignments;
Ability to understand and make work decisions in accordance with office rules, regulations, policies and procedures;
Ability to operate a personal computer using program applications appropriate to assigned duties and responsibilities;
Ability to work cooperatively and to maintain effective working relationships to accomplish job responsibilities;
Ability to quickly learn and put to use new skills and knowledge brought about by rapidly changing information and/or technology;
Ingenuity and inventiveness in the performance of assigned tasks.
 Acceptable Experience and Training:
Graduation from High School or GED, supplemented by additional course work in office management and data processing; and
Considerable experience in the performance of clerical and secretarial duties; or
Any equivalent combination of experience and training which provides the knowledge and abilities necessary to perform the work.

Job Description:
Reporting to the Director of Government Relations and Public Affairs, the Associate will work closely with the Director, the Companys various business groups and the executive team on various issues impacting the Company and its business.
The Associate will be responsible for helping build and maintain positive relationships with local, state and federal elected government officials.

RESPONSIBILITIES & ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
Assist in the development and execution by the Government Affairs team of local, state and federal legislative initiatives and other public policy strategies for the benefit of the Company;
Identify, analyze, review and communicate internally with respect to emerging legislative and other public policy initiatives at the local, state and federal level that pose potential liabilities or opportunities for the Company;
Assist in the development and execution of grass roots campaigns and other advocacy at the local, state and federal levels with respect to such initiatives;
Provide analytical review with respect to emerging legislation;
Collaborate with internal business groups on an ongoing basis to determine future needs and opportunities, ensure alignment of on-going Government Relations strategy and initiatives and to maximize business development;
Assist in the oversight and management of various third party trade groups; consultants, lobbyists, law firms and other individuals with respect to ongoing Government Affairs initiatives;
Develop and maintain on-going relationships at the community, local, state and federal level;
Perform budgetary planning and analysis;
Potential oversight of community partnership programs and other initiatives;
Able to serve on community boards and trade group committees, maintain leadership roles and regularly attend events outside of normal business hours;
Able to serve as a public face of the Company and express Company opinions and viewpoints;
Assist in the development and execution of the Companys alternative energy strategy;
Such other duties as may be developed and assigned from time to time.
Travel up to 25% of the time and work outside of normal business hours as needed.
QUALIFICATIONS:
BS/BA;
0-3 years of experience in state or federal government/government relations.
Ability to quickly develop relationships with local and state officials;
We are an equal opportunity employer. We consider applications for all positions without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, sexual orientation, citizenship status, genetic information or any other legally protected status.
